    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="530"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d530">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.796/367</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 4612</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-14">May 14,
                            1941</date>.<lb/>[Received May 21.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the activities of the
                    German-controlled Syndicate Condor airline in this country, I have the honor to
                    enclose a copy and translation of a confidential report<note n="62"
                        xml:id="d530fn1">Not printed.</note> submitted by the Brazilian Chief of
                    Staff, General Góes Monteiro, on May 9, 1941, to the Minister of War,
                    recommending that the recently established Condor service in the states of
                    Maranhão and Piauhy be suspended inasmuch as “these activities on the part of
                    the Syndicate Condor at the moment are prejudicial to the interests of national
                    defense.”</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Ambassador:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Randolph Harrison, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Second Secretary of Embassy</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
